  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Dottie, ?] in the meantime, worked in-- had got-- after she was liberated from the prison after a few weeks, and was in residence force-- that is forced residence in Caldes de Malevella-- she was sent on to Madrid.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Somehow, she wrote a letter to the-- to the wife of the ambassador, who was very impressed by this kind of letter, called her, and took a liking to [?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Dottie. ?] And [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Dottie ?] ask her to please try to help me to get out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was only possible if I was declared unfit for military service.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And for that purpose, I would have to be sent to a military hospital in-- it's a place nearby, and examined by four doctors.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "If they found that I-- that I was unfit for military service, I would be released, and could go to Madrid.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She-- the wife of the ambassador, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] through the influence she had with Spanish high government officials, achieved it in a relatively short time.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And-- and it must have been about the middle of March, I was suddenly called to come to the office.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And there, they told me, you will be sent to-- to a military hospital in Vitoria.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That was the name of the town.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I was examined there by a lieutenant doctor.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I somehow started a kind of kinship with him, and convinced him that-- that I was in great pain, that I had fallen in the Pyrenees, and I had-- I had formerly already had an accident, and it hurt, and et cetera.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "He said, I have to measure your legs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Only if one leg is shorter than the other, then-- then you will be declared unfit for military service.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
